/* ──────────────── i18n · Moments speaks your language ────────────────
   Every supported language has real, hand-written translations for the
   same key set — no language silently falls back to English because it
   was never filled in. Any KEY missing at runtime still falls back to
   English, then to the raw key, so nothing ever renders blank while
   this list keeps growing.

   RTL is real, not cosmetic: LanguageContext flips the document's
   writing direction on web, so switching to Arabic mirrors the whole
   layout (tab bar side, message bubbles, paddings) via the browser's
   own bidi engine — not just swapped words. */

